RAM:00C7             mem_next:                               ; CODE XREF: CHECK_FREE_MEM-189A↓j
RAM:00C7 23                          inc     hl
RAM:00C8 7C                          ld      a, h
RAM:00C9 B5                          or      l               ; continue until HL = $0000
RAM:00CA 28 1B                       jr      z, MEM_SIZE_END ; Reached top of memory. RAM exists all the way to $FFFF
RAM:00CC 7E                          ld      a, (hl)
RAM:00CD 47                          ld      b, a
RAM:00CE 2F                          cpl
RAM:00CF 77                          ld      (hl), a         ; save complemented value back
RAM:00D0 BE                          cp      (hl)            ; does it match? Yes if RAM exists at location
RAM:00D1 70                          ld      (hl), b
RAM:00D2 28 F3                       jr      z, mem_next
RAM:00D4 18 11                       jr      MEM_SIZE_END    ; no match, we have reached top of RAM
RAM:00D4             ; END OF FUNCTION CHUNK FOR CHECK_FREE_MEM

RAM:039B C9                          ret

RAM:03C2
RAM:03C2             DRIVER_ENTRY:                           ; CODE XREF: scan_keyboard:loc_46↑j
RAM:03C2 E5                          push    hl
RAM:03C3 DD E5                       push    ix
RAM:03C5 D5                          push    de              ; DE = DCB Address
RAM:03C6 DD E1                       pop     ix              ;  => IX
RAM:03C8 D5                          push    de
RAM:03C9 21 DD 03                    ld      hl, DRIVER_EXIT ; set return address
RAM:03CC E5                          push    hl
RAM:03CD 4F                          ld      c, a
RAM:03CE 1A                          ld      a, (de)         ; get first byte from DCB
RAM:03CF A0                          and     b               ; Isolate Device code bits
RAM:03D0 B8                          cp      b
RAM:03D1 C2 33 78                    jp      nz, byte_7833
RAM:03D4 FE 02                       cp      2
RAM:03D6 DD 6E 01                    ld      l, (ix+1)       ; get driver address from DCB
RAM:03D9 DD 66 02                    ld      h, (ix+2)
RAM:03DC E9                          jp      (hl)            ; Goto driver routine
RAM:03DC             ; END OF FUNCTION CHUNK FOR scan_keyboard
RAM:03DD             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:03DD
RAM:03DD             DRIVER_EXIT:                            ; DATA XREF: scan_keyboard+39E↑o
RAM:03DD D1                          pop     de              ; restore saved regs once driver call complete
RAM:03DE DD E1                       pop     ix
RAM:03E0 E1                          pop     hl
RAM:03E1 C1                          pop     bc
RAM:03E2 C9                          ret

RAM:03E3
RAM:03E3             loc_3E3:                                ; CODE XREF: RAM:04AB↓j
RAM:03E3                                                     ; sub_1BB3-1647↓p ...
RAM:03E3 21 39 78                    ld      hl, VID_CONTROL_BYTE
RAM:03E6 CB EE                       set     5, (hl)
RAM:03E8 2A 20 78                    ld      hl, (VIDEO_CURSOR_ADDRESS)
RAM:03EB CD 53 00                    call    GET_HL_CHAR     ; get the character at (HL) => A. Also saves in scratch location $783C
RAM:03EE 7C                          ld      a, h
RAM:03EF FE 71                       cp      71h ; 'q'
RAM:03F1 20 10                       jr      nz, not_last_line
RAM:03F3 7D                          ld      a, l
RAM:03F4 FE E0                       cp      0E0h
RAM:03F6 20 0B                       jr      nz, not_last_line
RAM:03F8 3A D7 7A                    ld      a, (LINE_DIRTY_ARRAY) ; Array is used to determine if lines have text showing. Affects scrolling.
RAM:03FB B7                          or      a
RAM:03FC 20 05                       jr      nz, not_last_line
RAM:03FE 3E 0D                       ld      a, 0Dh          ; Output a <CR>
RAM:0400 CD 8B 30                    call    CONSOLE_OUT
RAM:0403
RAM:0403             not_last_line:                          ; CODE XREF: RAM:03F1↑j
RAM:0403                                                     ; RAM:03F6↑j ...

RAM:0404 C5                          push    bc
RAM:0405 21 39 78                    ld      hl, VID_CONTROL_BYTE

RAM:040A CB 96                       res     2, (hl)
RAM:040C
RAM:040C             loc_40C:                                ; CODE XREF: RAM:040E↓j
RAM:040C CB 46                       bit     0, (hl)         ; waiting for vsync?
RAM:040E 28 FC                       jr      z, loc_40C      ; endless loop if this value isn't changed on interrupt chain!
RAM:0410

RAM:33A8             ; =============== S U B R O U T I N E =======================================
RAM:33A8
RAM:33A8             ; get "dirty bit" for current line => A
RAM:33A8
RAM:33A8             GET_CURR_LINE_DIRTY:                    ; CODE XREF: RAM:0431↑p
RAM:33A8                                                     ; RAM:0452↑p ...
RAM:33A8 3A A6 78                    ld      a, (CURSOR_COLUMN)
RAM:33AB 4F                          ld      c, a
RAM:33AC AF                          xor     a
RAM:33AD 47                          ld      b, a            ; BC = 00 + Cursor Column
RAM:33AE 2A 20 78                    ld      hl, (VIDEO_CURSOR_ADDRESS)
RAM:33B1 ED 42                       sbc     hl, bc          ; HL = start of current line now
RAM:33B3 E5                          push    hl
RAM:33B4 C1                          pop     bc              ; HL => BC
RAM:33B5 78                          ld      a, b            ; BC = 7000, 7020, 7040....71E0, 64col mode: 7000, 7040, 7080... 73C0
RAM:33B6 E6 0F                       and     0Fh             ; a = 0 or 1
RAM:33B8 CB 3F                       srl     a               ; a[0] to Carry
RAM:33BA 47                          ld      b, a            ; B now == ZERO
RAM:33BB CB 19                       rr      c               ; carry to C[7] and /2
RAM:33BD CB 39                       srl     c               ; /4
RAM:33BF CB 39                       srl     c               ; /8
RAM:33C1 CB 39                       srl     c               ; /16
RAM:33C3 CB 39                       srl     c               ; /32  BC now == 0-F
RAM:33C5 21 D7 7A                    ld      hl, LINE_DIRTY_ARRAY ; Array is used to determine if lines have text showing. Affects scrolling.
RAM:33C8 09                          add     hl, bc          ; BC index into table
RAM:33C9 7E                          ld      a, (hl)         ; get "dirty bit" for this line
RAM:33CA C9                          ret
RAM:33CA             ; End of function GET_CURR_LINE_DIRTY

RAM:4AD4 CD 13 59                    call    SEARCH          ; Search Directory for filename
RAM:4AD7 FE 02                       cp      2
RAM:4AD9 C2 41 42                    jp      nz, ERROR       ; Print Error Code in A and return to BASIC
RAM:4ADC C1                          pop     bc
RAM:4ADD E5                          push    hl
RAM:4ADE D5                          push    de
RAM:4ADF 69                          ld      l, c
RAM:4AE0 60                          ld      h, b
RAM:4AE1 CD 67 53                    call    CMD_STR_INTERPRETER
RAM:4AE4 D1                          pop     de
RAM:4AE5 E1                          pop     hl
RAM:4AE6 01 F8 FF                    ld      bc, 0FFF8h
RAM:4AE9 09                          add     hl, bc
RAM:4AEA EB                          ex      de, hl
RAM:4AEB 09                          add     hl, bc
RAM:4AEC 2B                          dec     hl
RAM:4AED 2B                          dec     hl
RAM:4AEE FD 7E 0A                    ld      a, (iy+10)
RAM:4AF1 77                          ld      (hl), a
RAM:4AF2 23                          inc     hl

RAM:4AF5 23                          inc     hl

RAM:4AFA ED B0                       ldir
RAM:4AFC CD A1 59                    call    WRITE_SECTOR

RAM:4B03 CD 52 5F                    call    PWROFF
RAM:4B06 E1                          pop     hl
RAM:4B07 C9                          ret
RAM:4B08             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:4B08
RAM:4B08             INIT:                                   ; CODE XREF: RAM:401A↑j
RAM:4B08                                                     ; DATA XREF: RAM:4385↑o
RAM:4B08 F3                          di                      ; Format Disk
RAM:4B09 CD 41 5F                    call    PWRON
RAM:4B0C C5                          push    bc
RAM:4B0D 01 E8 03                    ld      bc, 1000        ; 1 second: allow drive to come up to speed
RAM:4B10 CD BE 5E                    call    DELAY_BC_MS     ; Delay by BC millisecs
RAM:4B13 C1                          pop     bc
RAM:4B14 DB 13                       in      a, (13h)
RAM:4B16 B7                          or      a
RAM:4B17 3E 04                       ld      a, 4            ; Write Protect Error
RAM:4B19 FA 41 42                    jp      m, ERROR        ; Print Error Code in A and return to BASIC
RAM:4B1C E5                          push    hl
RAM:4B1D FD E5                       push    iy
RAM:4B1F E1                          pop     hl
RAM:4B20 11 4D 00                    ld      de, 4Dh ; 'M'
RAM:4B23 19                          add     hl, de
RAM:4B24 FD 36 12 00                 ld      (iy+18), 0      ; User Specified Track#
RAM:4B28 FD 36 11 00                 ld      (iy+17), 0      ; User Specified Sector#
RAM:4B2C FD 75 0E                    ld      (iy+14), l      ; User Buffer Address
RAM:4B2F FD 74 0F                    ld      (iy+15), h
RAM:4B32 EB                          ex      de, hl
RAM:4B33 21 4F 4D                    ld      hl, GAP1        ; GAP#1 definition bytes
RAM:4B36 01 18 00                    ld      bc, 24
RAM:4B39 ED B0                       ldir                    ; Copy GAP#1 and GAP#2 defs to the start of the buffer
RAM:4B3B 62                          ld      h, d
RAM:4B3C 6B                          ld      l, e
RAM:4B3D 36 00                       ld      (hl), 0
RAM:4B3F 13                          inc     de
RAM:4B40 01 82 00                    ld      bc, 130         ; 130 Bytes of ZERO == 128 Data + 2 byte checksum
RAM:4B43 ED B0                       ldir
RAM:4B45 FD 36 38 11                 ld      (iy+56), 11h    ; Stepper Phase
RAM:4B49 06 28                       ld      b, 40           ; Step out 40 times == restore to Track#0
RAM:4B4B CD 01 5F                    call    STEP_OUT        ; Step outwards to #tracks in B register
RAM:4B4E C5                          push    bc
RAM:4B4F 01 90 01                    ld      bc, 400
RAM:4B52 CD BE 5E                    call    DELAY_BC_MS     ; Delay by BC millisecs
RAM:4B55 C1                          pop     bc
RAM:4B56 FD 6E 0E                    ld      l, (iy+14)
RAM:4B59 FD 66 0F                    ld      h, (iy+15)      ; User Buffer Address
RAM:4B5C 11 0B 00                    ld      de, 0Bh
RAM:4B5F 19                          add     hl, de
RAM:4B60 54                          ld      d, h
RAM:4B61 5D                          ld      e, l
RAM:4B62 13                          inc     de              ; DE = pointer to TRACK# in IDAM buffer
RAM:4B63 42                          ld      b, d
RAM:4B64 4B                          ld      c, e
RAM:4B65 03                          inc     bc              ; BC = Pointer to Sector# in IDAM buffer
RAM:4B66 D9                          exx                     ; switch out to ALT reg set
RAM:4B67
RAM:4B67             format_next_track:                      ; CODE XREF: RAM:4CF6↓j
RAM:4B67 C5                          push    bc
RAM:4B68 01 64 00                    ld      bc, 100
RAM:4B6B CD BE 5E                    call    DELAY_BC_MS     ; Delay by BC millisecs
RAM:4B6E C1                          pop     bc
RAM:4B6F FD 7E 33                    ld      a, (iy+51)      ; LATCH
RAM:4B72 CB B7                       res     6, a            ; Turn on WRITEREQ
RAM:4B74 FD 77 33                    ld      (iy+51), a
RAM:4B77 D3 10                       out     (10h), a
RAM:4B79 C5                          push    bc
RAM:4B7A 01 64 00                    ld      bc, 100
RAM:4B7D CD BE 5E                    call    DELAY_BC_MS     ; Delay by BC millisecs
RAM:4B80 C1                          pop     bc
RAM:4B81 DD 21 67 4D                 ld      ix, SECTOR_SKEW_TABLE
RAM:4B85
RAM:4B85             next_sector:                            ; CODE XREF: RAM:4CD7↓j
RAM:4B85 FD 6E 0E                    ld      l, (iy+14)
RAM:4B88 FD 66 0F                    ld      h, (iy+15)      ; User Buffer Address => HL
RAM:4B8B FD 56 33                    ld      d, (iy+51)      ; copy of LATCH => D
RAM:4B8E 06 9A                       ld      b, 154          ; 154 bytes = GAP#1, ID, GAP#2, DATA, CHECKSUM
RAM:4B90
RAM:4B90             write_byte_init:                        ; CODE XREF: RAM:4CC4↓j
RAM:4B90 4E                          ld      c, (hl)         ; Byte to write => C
RAM:4B91 3E 20                       ld      a, 20h ; ' '
RAM:4B93 AA                          xor     d
RAM:4B94 CB 11                       rl      c               ; If bit is 1, we need to write a second pulse
RAM:4B96 D2 A4 4B                    jp      nc, bit7_zero
RAM:4B99 D3 10                       out     (10h), a        ; Always change phase for the clock bit
RAM:4B9B EE 20                       xor     20h ; ' '
RAM:4B9D 57                          ld      d, a
RAM:4B9E 2B                          dec     hl
RAM:4B9F D3 10                       out     (10h), a        ; Data bit == '1', so change phase *again*!
RAM:4BA1 C3 AF 4B                    jp      loc_4BAF
RAM:4BA4             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:4BA4
RAM:4BA4             bit7_zero:                              ; CODE XREF: RAM:4B96↑j
RAM:4BA4 D3 10                       out     (10h), a        ; Always change phase for the clock bit
RAM:4BA6 EE 00                       xor     0               ; do *nothing* to the latch output byte
RAM:4BA8 57                          ld      d, a
RAM:4BA9 2B                          dec     hl
RAM:4BAA D3 10                       out     (10h), a        ; Data bit is '0', so no second phase change!
RAM:4BAC C3 AF 4B                    jp      loc_4BAF
RAM:4BAF             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:4BAF
RAM:4BAF             loc_4BAF:                               ; CODE XREF: RAM:4BA1↑j

RAM:4BB6             loc_4BB6:                               ; CODE XREF: RAM:loc_4BB3↑j

RAM:4BB8 3E 20                       ld      a, 20h ; ' '
RAM:4BBA AA                          xor     d
RAM:4BBB CB 11                       rl      c               ; If bit is 1, we need to write a pulse
RAM:4BBD D2 CB 4B                    jp      nc, bit6_zero
RAM:4BC0 D3 10                       out     (10h), a        ; Start of clock bit: 11 T states
RAM:4BC2 EE 20                       xor     20h ; ' '       ; 7 T states
RAM:4BC4 57                          ld      d, a            ; 4 T states
RAM:4BC5 2B                          dec     hl              ; 6 T states
RAM:4BC6 D3 10                       out     (10h), a        ; 11 T states
RAM:4BC8 C3 D6 4B                    jp      loc_4BD6        ; 10 T states
RAM:4BCB             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:4BCB
RAM:4BCB             bit6_zero:                              ; CODE XREF: RAM:4BBD↑j
RAM:4BCB D3 10                       out     (10h), a        ; Start of clock bit: 11 T states

RAM:4BCF 57                          ld      d, a            ; 4 T states
RAM:4BD0 2B                          dec     hl              ; 6 T states

RAM:4BD3 C3 D6 4B                    jp      loc_4BD6        ; 10 T states

RAM:4CC0                                                     ; RAM:4CBD↑j
RAM:4CC0 23                          inc     hl
RAM:4CC1 23                          inc     hl
RAM:4CC2 00                          nop
RAM:4CC3 05                          dec     b               ; More bytes remaining to write?
RAM:4CC4 C2 90 4B                    jp      nz, write_byte_init
RAM:4CC7 FD 72 33                    ld      (iy+51), d
RAM:4CCA D9                          exx
RAM:4CCB DD 7E 01                    ld      a, (ix+1)       ; get next sector value from skew table
RAM:4CCE DD 23                       inc     ix
RAM:4CD0 12                          ld      (de), a         ; Update Sector# in format buffer
RAM:4CD1 86                          add     a, (hl)         ; Calc 1 byte checksum of track#+sector#
RAM:4CD2 02                          ld      (bc), a         ; Insert 1 byte checksum of Track#+Sector# in Format Buffer
RAM:4CD3 1A                          ld      a, (de)
RAM:4CD4 D9                          exx
RAM:4CD5 FE FF                       cp      0FFh            ; End of sector skew table?
RAM:4CD7 C2 85 4B                    jp      nz, next_sector
RAM:4CDA D9                          exx
RAM:4CDB AF                          xor     a
RAM:4CDC 12                          ld      (de), a         ; Sector# back to ZERO for next track
RAM:4CDD 7E                          ld      a, (hl)         ; Increment Track number in data buffer
RAM:4CDE 3C                          inc     a
RAM:4CDF 77                          ld      (hl), a         ; Save new track# in Format Buffer
RAM:4CE0 02                          ld      (bc), a         ; Since Sector# is currently ZERO, checksum will be same as Track# :o)
RAM:4CE1 D9                          exx
RAM:4CE2 FE 28                       cp      40              ; More tracks left? 0-39 valid
RAM:4CE4 CA F9 4C                    jp      z, all_tracks_formatted
RAM:4CE7 FD 7E 33                    ld      a, (iy+51)      ; get LATCH value
RAM:4CEA F6 40                       or      40h ; '@'       ; Turn *off* the WRITEREQ signal while stepping between tracks!
RAM:4CEC FD 77 33                    ld      (iy+51), a
RAM:4CEF D3 10                       out     (10h), a
RAM:4CF1 06 01                       ld      b, 1
RAM:4CF3 CD CE 5E                    call    STEP_IN         ; Step inwards to #tracks in B register
RAM:4CF6 C3 67 4B                    jp      format_next_track
RAM:4CF9             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:4CF9
RAM:4CF9             all_tracks_formatted:                   ; CODE XREF: RAM:4CE4↑j
RAM:4CF9 FD 7E 33                    ld      a, (iy+51)      ; Copy of LATCH
RAM:4CFC F6 40                       or      40h ; '@'       ; WriteREQ OFF
RAM:4CFE FD 77 33                    ld      (iy+51), a
RAM:4D01 D3 10                       out     (10h), a
RAM:4D03 06 27                       ld      b, 39           ; Back to Track #0
RAM:4D05 CD 01 5F                    call    STEP_OUT        ; Step outwards to #tracks in B register
RAM:4D08 FD 36 12 00                 ld      (iy+18), 0
RAM:4D0C FD 36 11 00                 ld      (iy+17), 0      ; Reset Track/Sector Numbers
RAM:4D10
RAM:4D10             verify_next_track:                      ; CODE XREF: RAM:4D39↓j
RAM:4D10 DD 21 67 4D                 ld      ix, SECTOR_SKEW_TABLE
RAM:4D14
RAM:4D14             verify_next_sector:                     ; CODE XREF: RAM:4D23↓j
RAM:4D14 CD EA 53                    call    READ_ID_ADDRESS_MARK ; Verify disk by reading ID field of every Track/Sector
RAM:4D17 20 2C                       jr      nz, INIT_ERROR
RAM:4D19 DD 7E 01                    ld      a, (ix+1)
RAM:4D1C DD 23                       inc     ix
RAM:4D1E FD 77 11                    ld      (iy+17), a
RAM:4D21 FE FF                       cp      0FFh            ; past end of Sector Skew Table?
RAM:4D23 20 EF                       jr      nz, verify_next_sector
RAM:4D25 AF                          xor     a
RAM:4D26 FD 77 11                    ld      (iy+17), a
RAM:4D29 FD 7E 12                    ld      a, (iy+18)
RAM:4D2C 3C                          inc     a
RAM:4D2D FD 77 12                    ld      (iy+18), a
RAM:4D30 FE 28                       cp      40              ; Reached Track#40?
RAM:4D32 28 07                       jr      z, INIT_SUCCESS
RAM:4D34 06 01                       ld      b, 1
RAM:4D36 CD CE 5E                    call    STEP_IN         ; Step inwards to #tracks in B register
RAM:4D39 18 D5                       jr      verify_next_track
RAM:4D3B             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:4D3B
RAM:4D3B             INIT_SUCCESS:                           ; CODE XREF: RAM:4D32↑j
RAM:4D3B 06 27                       ld      b, 39
RAM:4D3D CD 01 5F                    call    STEP_OUT        ; Step outwards to #tracks in B register
RAM:4D40 CD 52 5F                    call    PWROFF
RAM:4D43 E1                          pop     hl
RAM:4D44 C9                          ret
RAM:4D45             ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RAM:4D45
RAM:4D45             INIT_ERROR:                             ; CODE XREF: RAM:4D17↑j
RAM:4D45 FE 11                       cp      17

RAM:5B10
RAM:5B10             CALC_CHECKSUM:                          ; CODE XREF: WRITE_SECTOR↑p
RAM:5B10                                                     ; READ_SECTOR:all_bytes_read↓p

RAM:5B1C
RAM:5B1C             loc_5B1C:                               ; CODE XREF: CALC_CHECKSUM+14↓j

RAM:5B1D 7B                          ld      a, e
RAM:5B1E 86                          add     a, (hl)
RAM:5B1F 5F                          ld      e, a
RAM:5B20 3E 00                       ld      a, 0
RAM:5B22 8A                          adc     a, d
RAM:5B23 57                          ld      d, a            ; DE = total of all bytes added together
RAM:5B24 10 F6                       djnz    loc_5B1C
RAM:5B26 C9                          ret
RAM:5B26             ; End of function CALC_CHECKSUM
